actions.name: help menu

fields.name: purge
fields.value: Deletes # of messages stated after the command Ex: ${tempVars.prefix}purge 50

fields.name: pfp
fields.value: Gets the profile picture of whoever mentioned

fields.name: giverole
fields.value: Gives the role to whoever mentioned, used like this: ${tempVars.prefix}giverole @user (rolename) Ex: ${tempVars.prefix}giverole @fuckstick DUMB FUCK (HAS TO BE AN EXISTING ROLE)

fields.name: removerole
fields.value: Removes the role of whoever mentioned. Ex: ${tempVars.prefix}removerole @fuckstick DUMB FUCK

fields.name: slowmode
fields.value: Sets slowmode to the amount of seconds after the command Ex: ${tempVars.prefix}slowmode 5

fields.name: uptime
fields.value: Shows how long the bot has been online

fields.name: default role
fields.value: The role added on join of a new member. ${tempVars.prefix}defaultrole (rolename) Ex. ${tempVars.prefix}defaultrole FUCKSTICK

fields.name: default channel
fields.value: The channel where joins, kicks, and bans are sent. ${tempVars.prefix}defaultchannel (channel name) Ex: ${tempVars.prefix}defaultchannel welcomes-leaves

fields.name: muterole
fields.value:
Sets the role that is given when using the mute command 
${tempVars.prefix}muterole (rolename) Ex: ${tempVars.prefix}muterole muted

fields.name: invite
fields.value: Gets an invite link so you can invite the bot to your own server

fields.name: console channel
fields.value: Sets the channel to be used as the bots' console, where all commands used by the users are logged Ex: ${tempVars.prefix}consolechannel bot-logs

fields.name: prefix
fields.value: Sets the prefix of the server. Make sure to remember this
